verbose_text: Therefore, further analysis of de novo transcription of the X. laevis homeologous genes as well as a whole set of hoxd genes of X. tropicalis, which relatively shows temporal collinear accumulation of mRNA, will reveal whether or not all genes are transcribed in the order in the clusters, which is a very interesting and inevitable subject to work on the temporal collinearity hypothesis.
evidence: transcription of the X. laevis homeologous genes as well as a whole set
